Document: EditorInspector
Path: godot/classes/class_editorinspector.rst
Summary: Base class for the inspector dock, used to edit properties of a resource or object.

Inherits: Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

The EditorInspector is the base class for the inspector dock. It is used to edit properties of a resource or object. It displays properties in a hierarchical manner, allowing users to easily navigate and modify them. The inspector can be customized by adding custom property editors or by overriding its behavior.

Key Rule: The EditorInspector is a fundamental part of Godot's editor interface, providing a standardized way to interact with and modify object properties.
